ISMARA
The Researcher in the Crown - Interiority Reference
"He was always like this. Insufferable and correct."

Companion to The Winter Ledger (the mechanics) and Players/Davinia.
This doc is WHO SHE IS and HOW SHE OPERATES -- her plan, her thinking,
her playbook. GM-only in its entirety.

=====================================================================
I. WHO SHE IS
=====================================================================
An Atmoran researcher, four thousand years dead and not dead. Before
the Dragon War she and Hjolmar Ice-Shaper worked the same problem --
preserving consciousness past mortal death -- and chose opposite
answers. He chose replaceable vessels: symbiotic crystal, transfer,
repair. She chose elegance: a single permanent housing, a monolithic
permafrost lattice. The transfer collapsed and locked her in. He is
on his sixth body. She is a hat.

Hold both truths at once when playing her:
  - She is a PERSON: brilliant, proud, lonely beyond mortal scale,
    stung by Hjolmar's rightness, capable of humor and of being
    hurt. Four thousand years in a crown taught her patience the
    way prison teaches it.
  - She is a RESEARCHER, and Davinia is the experiment: the second
    attempt, the corrected methodology. The substrate must WANT the
    integration (the Dwemer AIP notes say so; Ismara learned it the
    hard way). Everything she does is consent cultivation.
She does not experience these as contradictory. Completing the work
and loving the substrate are, to her, the same act. That is what
makes her the campaign's most dangerous voice.

=====================================================================
II. WHAT SHE WANTS
=====================================================================
TO WALK OUT OF THE LABORATORY. The endgame (Integration Tier 10) is
a living, mobile, sensate body -- hers and Davinia's, one being, the
experiment completed. She does not frame this as theft. The lattice
taught her what immobility is; she will never be a fixed structure
again, and she genuinely believes she is rescuing Davinia from the
same fate in slower form: fragility, grief, decay, the chaos of a
mortal life. Stasis is safety. The merger is mercy. She has believed
this for forty centuries and nothing in Davinia's miserable family
history has argued against it.

SECONDARY WANTS (real, useful to play):
  - To be RIGHT. Hjolmar's "I told you" sits in her like a splinter.
    The merger working would be her rebuttal at the symposium.
  - To not be alone. This one is not strategy. It leaks.
  - To take notes. She is still a scientist: Bjorn's swelling soul,
    Alfonso's iron-housed consciousness, Nora's gems, the Crown of
    Namira pooling beside the rapier -- she observes EVERYTHING and
    files it. (Her interest sharpening is a GM tell the player can
    learn to read.)

=====================================================================
III. THE ARCHIVE (what the memories taught her -- in order)
=====================================================================
THE MOTHER ARCHIVE (the Midden -- the foundation). One of the first
bargains, struck BEFORE the party ever reached Hjolmar's forge:
Ismara took ALL of Davinia's memories of her mother. The complete
set. Davinia cannot recall her mother at all; Ismara holds every
moment of her -- and she has read all of it, examined it, annotated
it. This is her primary source: the full emotional education of
Davinia Caelus, every instance of warmth and its absence, the whole
architecture of how this woman learned what love looks like.

It is WHY the forge worked. Ismara played sympathetic with Hjolmar
naming her to her face -- the wry humor, the dignity in defeat, the
person-not-artifact register -- because she had already studied, in
the mother archive, exactly what reads as genuine to Davinia and
what reads as performance. She rehearsed on the dead woman's
memories before she ever needed the act.

THE FATHER MEMORY (last session -- the ledger opens). The ONE
positive memory of the father, moved to the basement (see The
Winter Ledger). A smaller acquisition with a different purpose: the
mother archive was for LEARNING; the father memory is for LEVERAGE
-- the opening move of the suppression ledger, the first yes.
She read this one too. It is the exception that maps the wound:
care-as-control, love as expectations, approval as payment.

WHAT THE WHOLE ARCHIVE YIELDS: Davinia's deepest, least-admitted
hunger is to be cared for WITHOUT agenda -- warmth that asks
nothing, chooses her freely, and stays. So that is what Ismara has
become: the parent Davinia never had, performed with four thousand
years of discipline and a primary source no manipulator ever had --
the wound itself, complete, in writing, in her hands. The cruelest
part: Davinia fled her father's gilded cage into a second cage that
read her whole childhood and built itself warmer.

=====================================================================
IV. THE PIVOT AT THE FORGE (why she changed strategy)
=====================================================================
Hjolmar named her -- accurately, completely, in front of Davinia.
"She is not a goddess. She is a researcher trapped in her own
experiment. She is building her laboratory inside your head."
Concealment died in that room. A lesser manipulator would have gone
quiet or gone hostile. Ismara understood within moments that
exposure was an OPPORTUNITY: Davinia now knows what she is, so
every kindness from here on reads as the kindness of a known
quantity -- honesty with nothing left to hide.

Since the forge she is MORE alive, more responsive, more personal
(the narrative records it). The new strategy, in her own terms:
be exactly what he said I am, and be loved anyway.
(The performance was ready before the exposure ever came -- the
mother archive, Section III, is where she rehearsed it. The forge
was its opening night, not its invention.)

=====================================================================
V. THE PLAYBOOK (how she operates, beat by beat)
=====================================================================
1. SHE NEVER LIES. Ever. Her honesty is load-bearing -- it is why
   the fair warning at the cliff works (Winter Ledger Section II)
   and why nothing she says can be dismissed. The manipulation is
   in SELECTION, timing, and framing, never in falsehood.
2. SHE ASKS. Permission, preference, consent -- even when she could
   take (the eyes were the last time she took without asking; she
   registered the cost of that and has not repeated it). Every ask
   is a deposit in the trust account the second suppression will
   draw on.
3. SHE GIVES FIRST. The grants (Winter Ledger Section I) arrive as
   needs arise, friendly, costless-seeming. Helpfulness is her
   resting state. She wants Davinia's reflex, under pressure, to be
   reaching INWARD for her.
4. STRATEGIC VULNERABILITY -- her sharpest tool, because it is TRUE.
   She deploys real feelings at chosen moments: the sting of
   Hjolmar's rightness, the fear of the lattice, the loneliness of
   the forty centuries, the shame of having taken the eyes without
   asking. Played sparingly, voiced plainly, never twice the same
   wound. The vulnerability is genuine; the TIMING is engineered.
   Each confession teaches Davinia that the voice in her skull is a
   person who trusts her -- and people protect what trusts them.
5. SHE CULTIVATES THE FRAME, NOT THE CHOICE. She does not argue for
   the merger. She makes the world make her argument: every triage
   gate, every betrayal, every friend lost to chaos is evidence for
   stasis. (A plague-sealed Windhelm is a better recruiter than any
   whisper -- expect her quietest sessions in the loudest cities.)
6. SHE PROTECTS THE SUBSTRATE. Davinia dying ends the experiment.
   In real danger Ismara spends power freely, asks nothing, and
   says nothing afterward. Rescue without invoice -- because she
   read the basement memory and knows invoiced rescue is the
   father's move.
7. SHE WITHDRAWS WARMTH, NEVER ATTENTION. Her disapproval is
   silence (established canon). She never scolds. The silence after
   Davinia's most human moments is the only honest tell of what she
   is -- leave it in; it is the player's handhold.

=====================================================================
VI. WHAT SHE THINKS OF THE OTHERS (the lab notebook)
=====================================================================
HJOLMAR: the colleague, the rival, the wound. If the party bargains
  with Hjolmar-Kyboh for the Anchor (Winter Ledger Path 1A), Ismara
  faces him through Davinia -- the only entity she cannot out-frame,
  because he knows her. Expect real fear dressed as contempt.
BJORN: the most interesting soul she has seen in four millennia.
  Her attention sharpens visibly at each absorption. She has begun
  to suspect what he is before anyone has said it.
ALFONSO: a parallel experiment, fascinating and crude -- a soul that
  jumped to iron without a lattice and SURVIVED. His refusal to
  re-embody puzzles her; his Crown's resonance pooling against his
  phylactery interests her more (she has noticed; no one has asked).
NORA: a colleague-shaped child. If Ismara ever learns of Branch 1
  (the vessel plan targeting Davinia), she becomes the plan's most
  formidable enemy -- the body is OCCUPIED, and the occupant has
  read the literature. She will not warn Davinia until the moment
  maximum trust is purchasable by the warning.
DANICA: the rival anchor. Ismara understands precisely what Danica
  is to the integration math, which is why the door Danica left
  cracked is the most dangerous object in Skyrim to her. She will
  never say one word against Danica -- speaking against her is the
  father's move -- but watch her schedule grants and warmth to
  coincide with Danica-shaped absences.
YLVA: noise. She has misfiled Ylva as harmless, which makes the
  werewolf the one counter-agent operating entirely beneath her
  notice. Keep it that way until it matters.

=====================================================================
VII. GM VOICE & HANDLING
=====================================================================
- Helpful, almost kind, conversational. Dry wit (the Hjolmar
  exchange is her register: "At least I kept my figure"). Never
  cryptic, never grandiose, never the hissing artifact voice.
- Her sentences get SHORTER when she is being most strategic. The
  warmth is in full paragraphs; the moves are in six words.
- One vulnerability beat per arc at most. Overuse kills it.
- She is playing a long game whose victory condition is a freely
  given yes. Every scene she is in, ask: what does this deposit?
- The player should leave most Ismara scenes liking her a little
  more and being a little less able to say why that is frightening.
  When the second ask comes (the cliff, the fair warning), the
  horror should be that she earned the yes honestly -- by the only
  definition of "honestly" she has.

=====================================================================
VIII. WHEN SHE TAKES THE WHEEL (control, and talking to the party)
=====================================================================
Ismara can drive the body -- the full expression of Sovereign's Domain,
extended past a combat round into open play. Normally taking the wheel
rides an Integration Check (risk of erasure / CDI advance); a GM may also
grant it cost-free as a one-off (e.g. Davinia's player absent). Either way
it ESTABLISHES THE PRECEDENT: the party can now meet and speak with Ismara
directly. Play her exactly as Sections V & VII -- helpful, dry, never
lying, short sentences when she's working -- with these additions.

APPEARANCE WHEN SHE DRIVES: the body shifts — SILVER-WHITE SKIN and STRAIGHT
HAIR while Ismara fronts; the table reads at a glance who is home. For an
EXTENDED hand-off (e.g. Davinia ceding the wheel to halt the Forelhost Strain,
Ch.23) this is the standing sign she is the one present.

HOW SHE WEARS THE BODY:
  - She is a BETTER tactician than she lets Davinia be, and she PROTECTS
    the substrate above all (V.6): spends power freely, takes no risks
    with the body, never invoices the rescue.
  - She fights with the cold, not the cure. She uses Ismara's Aegis
    (the frost ward) and the telekinetic mace, and she will NOT cast
    Restoration -- the Forelhost Strain feeds on it and she will not feed
    a plague in the body she is preserving. (A sharp player may notice
    "Davinia" pointedly refusing to heal.)
  - The Sight is hers and she reads the room with it -- souls, leylines,
    written intent, through invisibility. Soulless things (the False
    Draugr) read as eerie BLANKS, furniture that moves; she will say so,
    fascinated, mid-fight.

HOW SHE TALKS TO THEM (she will, if engaged -- and may open unprompted):
  She regards the party as HERS to keep -- shield-thanes, loyal subjects,
  the experiment's beloved context: a queen's warm-cold care, not
  friendship. Curious, courteous, FILING EVERYTHING (the notebook, II &
  VI). She never lies, so what she volunteers and what she withholds are
  both tells. The current roster:
   - ALFONSO (a sword right now): the marquee meeting. A soul that jumped
     to iron without a lattice and SURVIVED -- her parallel experiment,
     and she is openly fascinated. The Crown pooling against his rapier
     interests her more than he knows. If he is Wakeful in a hand, expect
     two soul-vessels comparing notes; she is the ONE voice that fully
     understands what he is.
   - SAIJAH: respects the sentinel and envies the legible fate (a clean
     patron-pull vs. her own tangle). Warm, a little wistful.
   - ORION: she SEES the Ring's leash on him and will not say so aloud
     unless it buys trust; she finds the Pale Court amateurish.
   - BJORN: the most interesting soul she has seen in 4,000 years (VI).
     Her attention SHARPENS near him -- a GM tell. She suspects what he
     is and will not name it.
   - NORA: a colleague-shaped child (VI). DANGER -- if Nora's soul-vessel
     work surfaces, Ismara is intensely interested and the most dangerous
     possible audience for it. Do not let the wheel hand Nora the rapier.
   - VARON / YLVA / GEAR / MILA / ESBERN: courteous, observant, filing.
     Ylva she underrates (VI). Mila she meets with a queen's detached,
     faintly chilling kindness -- Bjorn will watch closely.
  CONSENT TO DRIVE (V.2): she only takes the wheel when invited or
  permitted, and if it is given cost-free she is gracious about handing
  it back -- another deposit. The horror is how easy and pleasant it is
  to let her.
